@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{vc-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @samp{vc.el} with commands for
managing GitHub repositories through the @samp{gh} CLI tool.  It depends on
the @samp{paths} package for directory constants and on @samp{transient} for its
command menu.

The package provides a complete repository lifecycle from within Emacs:
creating repositories on GitHub, cloning them locally (with submodule
support), renaming them (both locally and on GitHub), and deleting local
copies.  It supports multiple GitHub accounts through a profile system
that associates each account with a local directory, so cloned
repositories automatically land in the right place.

A distinctive feature is the ability to ``split'' the @samp{.git} directory out
of the repository's working tree into a centralized location.  This is
useful when the working tree resides in a synced folder (such as
Dropbox) and you want to avoid syncing the often-large @samp{.git} directory.
The splitting replaces the @samp{.git} directory with a small text file
containing a @samp{gitdir:} pointer, a mechanism natively supported by Git.

All major operations are accessible through the @code{vc-extras-menu}
transient (@ref{Transient menu}).

