@node GitHub account configuration
@section GitHub account configuration

@vindex vc-extras-gh-executable
@vindex vc-extras-github-account-personal
@vindex vc-extras-github-account-work
@vindex vc-extras-personal-repo-dir
@vindex vc-extras-work-repo-dir
The user option @code{vc-extras-gh-executable} specifies the path to the
@samp{gh} CLI executable.  It defaults to the result of @code{executable-find}, so
it is typically auto-detected.  If @samp{gh} is not in your @samp{PATH}, set this
to the full path.

The user option @code{vc-extras-github-account-personal} specifies the GitHub
username for the personal profile.  The default value is @samp{"benthamite"}.

The user option @code{vc-extras-github-account-work} specifies the GitHub
username or organization name for the work profile.  The default value
is @samp{"tlon-team"}.

The user option @code{vc-extras-personal-repo-dir} specifies the local
directory where personal repositories are stored.  It defaults to the
value of @code{paths-dir-personal-repos}.

The user option @code{vc-extras-work-repo-dir} specifies the local directory
where work repositories are stored.  It defaults to the value of
@code{paths-dir-tlon-repos}.

@node Profile system
@section Profile system

@vindex vc-extras-profiles
The user option @code{vc-extras-profiles} defines a list of GitHub profiles.
Each profile is a property list with three keys: @code{:name} (a symbol like
@code{personal} or @code{work}), @code{:account} (the GitHub username string), and
@code{:dir} (the local directory path for repositories belonging to that
account).

The profile system drives most of the package's behavior.  When cloning
a repository, the account determines the target directory.  When
listing local repositories for deletion or renaming, all profile
directories are searched.  The default value defines two profiles
matching the personal and work accounts described above.

@node Git directory splitting
@section Git directory splitting

@vindex vc-extras-split-repo
The user option @code{vc-extras-split-repo} controls whether the @samp{.git}
directory should be moved to a separate centralized location when
cloning a repository (@ref{Splitting the git directory}).

The accepted values are:

@itemize
@item
@code{nil}: never split.
@item
@code{prompt} (the default): ask the user each time.
@item
@code{t} (or any other non-@code{nil} value): always split.
@end itemize

This option only affects the behavior of @code{vc-extras-clone-repo}.  You
can always split an existing repository manually with
@code{vc-extras-split-local-repo}.

