@node Creating repositories
@section Creating repositories

@findex vc-extras-create-repo
The command @code{vc-extras-create-repo} creates a new repository on GitHub
using the @samp{gh} CLI@.  It prompts for a name, an account (from the
profiles in @code{vc-extras-profiles}), a description, and whether the
repository should be private.  After creation, it offers to clone the
new repository locally using @code{vc-extras-clone-repo}
(@ref{Cloning repositories}).

@node Cloning repositories
@section Cloning repositories

@findex vc-extras-clone-repo
The command @code{vc-extras-clone-repo} clones a GitHub repository into the
local directory associated with the repository's account.  When called
without arguments, it fetches the list of repositories from GitHub (via
@samp{gh repo list}) and presents them for completion.

The clone uses @samp{git clone --recurse-submodules} to ensure submodules
are initialized.  After cloning, the command:

@enumerate
@item
Initializes and updates submodules, then checks out the default
branch (@samp{main} or @samp{master}) in each submodule.
@item
Optionally splits the @samp{.git} directory based on the
@code{vc-extras-split-repo} user option (@ref{Git directory splitting}).
@item
Optionally prompts to add the repository to Forge (via
@code{forge-extras-track-repository}), unless the NO-FORGE argument is
non-@code{nil}.
@end enumerate

With a prefix argument, the command prompts for the parent directory
instead of using the account's default directory.

The clone runs asynchronously and reports progress via messages.

@node Renaming repositories
@section Renaming repositories

@findex vc-extras-rename-repo
The command @code{vc-extras-rename-repo} renames a repository both locally
and on GitHub.  It prompts for the repository to rename (with
completion from local repositories), the new name, and the account if
it cannot be determined automatically.

The command performs four operations:

@enumerate
@item
Renames the local directory.
@item
Renames the split @samp{.git} directory (if one exists) and updates the
@samp{.git} pointer file.
@item
Renames the repository on GitHub via the @samp{gh} API@.
@item
Updates the Git remote URL in the local configuration.
@end enumerate

If any step fails (e.g., the remote rename returns an error), the
command reports a warning but continues with the remaining steps.

@node Deleting local repositories
@section Deleting local repositories

@findex vc-extras-delete-local-repo
The command @code{vc-extras-delete-local-repo} deletes a local Git
repository.  It prompts for the repository name with completion from
all local Git repositories found in the profile directories.

The command deletes both the main repository directory (if it exists and
is a Git repository) and the corresponding split @samp{.git} directory in
@code{paths-dir-split-git} (if it exists).  A message lists the directories
that were actually deleted.

@node Splitting the git directory
@section Splitting the git directory

@findex vc-extras-split-local-repo
The command @code{vc-extras-split-local-repo} moves the @samp{.git} directory
from a repository to a centralized location under @code{paths-dir-split-git}
and replaces it with a @samp{.git} file containing a @samp{gitdir:} pointer.
This is useful when the working tree is in a synced folder (e.g.,
Dropbox) and you want to avoid syncing the potentially large @samp{.git}
directory.

If the repository has submodules, the command also updates their @samp{.git}
pointer files and runs @code{git submodule sync --recursive} to ensure
everything remains consistent.

@node Checking authentication
@section Checking authentication

@findex vc-extras-check-gh-authenticated
The command @code{vc-extras-check-gh-authenticated} verifies that the @samp{gh}
CLI is properly authenticated by running @samp{gh auth status}.  It displays
a success message or signals an error with instructions to authenticate.

@node Stripping diff markers
@section Stripping diff markers

@findex vc-extras-strip-diff-markers
The command @code{vc-extras-strip-diff-markers} removes leading @samp{+} or @samp{-}
characters from each line in the active region.  This is useful when you
paste diff output into a buffer and want to clean it up into plain text.

@node Transient menu
@section Transient menu

@findex vc-extras-menu
The command @code{vc-extras-menu} presents a transient menu providing quick
access to all major @samp{vc-extras} commands: creating, cloning (with and
without directory confirmation), splitting, renaming, deleting, and
checking authentication status.

