@node Repository information
@section Repository information

@findex vc-extras-is-git-dir-p
@findex vc-extras-has-submodules-p
@findex vc-extras-get-github-remote
@findex vc-extras-get-account-of-name
@findex vc-extras-get-account-prop
@findex vc-extras-get-repo-dir
@findex vc-extras-resolve-repo-dir
@findex vc-extras-list-local-candidates
The function @code{vc-extras-is-git-dir-p} returns non-@code{nil} if a directory
is recognized as a Git repository by @code{vc-responsible-backend}.

The function @code{vc-extras-has-submodules-p} checks whether a @samp{.gitmodules}
file exists in a directory, indicating that the repository has
submodules.

The function @code{vc-extras-get-github-remote} constructs the HTTPS GitHub
remote URL for a repository name and account.

The function @code{vc-extras-get-account-of-name} determines which GitHub
account owns a repository by querying @samp{gh repo list} for each profile.

The function @code{vc-extras-get-account-prop} retrieves a property (such as
@code{:dir}) for a given account from @code{vc-extras-profiles}.

The function @code{vc-extras-get-repo-dir} constructs the local path for a
repository, optionally pointing to the @samp{.git} or split @samp{.git}
directory.

The function @code{vc-extras-resolve-repo-dir} looks up a repository's local
directory from a candidates alist or constructs it from the account.

The function @code{vc-extras-list-local-candidates} returns an alist of
@samp{(NAME . DIR)} pairs for all local Git repositories found in the profile
directories.

@node GitHub CLI operations
@section GitHub CLI operations

@findex vc-extras-gh-create-repo
@findex vc-extras-ensure-gh-exists
@findex vc-extras-gh-list-repos
@findex vc-extras-gh-list-repos-in-account
@findex vc-extras-gh-list-repos-in-all-accounts
The function @code{vc-extras-gh-create-repo} executes the @samp{gh repo create}
command with the given name, account, description, and visibility.

The function @code{vc-extras-ensure-gh-exists} signals an error if @samp{gh} is
not installed.

The function @code{vc-extras-gh-list-repos} lists repositories for a
specific account or all accounts.  It delegates to
@code{vc-extras-gh-list-repos-in-account} and
@code{vc-extras-gh-list-repos-in-all-accounts}.

